  "logTail": [
    {
      "channel": "narration",
      "text": "You have started to keep count of your own strength — what the day has drawn out of you, and how far that is from Sōan's pallet.",
      "count": 1
    },
    {
      "channel": "narration",
      "text": "The kura's count is open to you now: rice in, rice out, and the thin line between the store and a lean winter.",
      "count": 1
    },
    {
      "channel": "narration",
      "text": "\"How long was I in the river?\"",
      "count": 1,
      "speaker": "You"
    },
    {
      "channel": "narration",
      "text": "\"That I can't write down. Three days here, fevered. Before that, ask the river.\"",
      "count": 1,
      "speaker": "Sōan"
    },
    {
      "channel": "narration",
      "text": "\"The work. Point me at it.\"",
      "count": 1,
      "speaker": "You"
    },
    {
      "channel": "narration",
      "text": "\"Can you stand? Then the rake is by the door, and the well is past the kitchen. Water first — the kitchen never has enough. Come back when something bleeds.\"",
      "count": 1,
      "speaker": "Sōan"
    },
    {
      "channel": "milestone",
      "text": "Perk unlocked — The Well Yoke: a load the shoulders carry before it is asked. (+1 STR / −1 LUCK)",
      "count": 1
    },
    {
      "channel": "reward",
      "text": "You rake the spilled rice back toward the basket. (+2 rice)",
      "count": 1
    },
    {
      "channel": "narration",
      "text": "So you put your hands to it. Rake what grain is still whole back toward the basket, a fistful at a time. We reckon a samurai house’s worth in koku — a year’s eating for one man — and every basket you save us is a measure we need not go begging to the lord to make good.",
      "count": 1,
      "speaker": "Genemon"
    },
    {
      "channel": "narration",
      "text": "You can stop now, when the day is done — set the work down, and let the body take back what it can.",
      "count": 1
    },
    {
      "channel": "reward",
      "text": "You rake the spilled rice back toward the basket. (+2 rice)",
      "count": 1
    },
    {
      "channel": "narration",
      "text": "Clear it without my standing over you, and you'll have earned your rice and a dry corner to sleep in. I'll make you no grander promise than that. In this house, none of us holds one.",
      "count": 1,
      "speaker": "Genemon"
    },
    {
      "channel": "reward",
      "text": "You rake the spilled rice back toward the basket. (+2 rice)",
      "count": 1
    },
    {
      "channel": "narration",
      "text": "\"...You don't shirk the work,\" Genemon says, eyeing the cleared boards and the filling basket. \"The house has had its fill of hands that do. Earn your keep, and a place here is yours.\"",
      "count": 1
    },
    {
      "channel": "reward",
      "text": "You rake the spilled rice back toward the basket. (+2 rice)",
      "count": 2
    },
    {
      "channel": "system",
      "text": "You lie down in the bare corner of the woodshed — no mat yet, the woodpile at your back, the cold coming up through the boards. It is somewhere to stop.",
      "count": 1
    },
    {
      "channel": "reward",
      "text": "You rake the spilled rice back toward the basket. (+2 rice)",
      "count": 2
    },
    {
      "channel": "system",
